    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Engine Electrical Components - Description of Engine Electrical Components -
        Chassis Mounted - EGR Drive Module (Exhaust Gas Recirculation)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.3.2" graphiccount="1">
        <title>EGR Drive Module (Exhaust Gas Recirculation)</title>
        <figure id="e3001138" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>EGR drive module</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EGR drive module controls the EGR actuator. The EGR drive module receives the desired EGR valve
            position from the ECM to activate the valve for exhaust gas recirculation. The EGR drive module provides
            feedback to the ECM on the valve position. The EGR drive module is typically located near the ECM / IDM
            assembly for CF and stripped chassis applications.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
